1. Download the latest Ubuntu Precise Pangolin Server 64bit install ISO image

2. Create a boot media with unetbootin (/dev/sdb1 in this example)

3. Install preseed files:

  mkdir /media/usbstick
  mount /dev/sdb1 /media/usbstick
  ./install.sh /media/usbstick
  cp /media/usbstick/menu.c32 /media/usbstick/vesamenu.c32
  umount /dev/sdb1

Then just plug it in, boot and wait until the installation is finished.
